I'll do much better
next time.

259
00:12:19,472 --> 00:12:21,539
[ Laughs ]

260
00:12:23,475 --> 00:12:25,776
[ All murmuring ]

261
00:12:25,778 --> 00:12:27,845
Who's gonna tell Sybil
this time?

262
00:12:27,847 --> 00:12:30,982
Forget about, Sybil.
What about Eddie?

263
00:12:30,984 --> 00:12:33,384
[ Indistinct talking ]

264
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:46,564
Oh, Mr. fisher.

265
00:12:46,566 --> 00:12:49,834
I think you'll find Miss Taylor
in makeup.

266
00:12:49,836 --> 00:12:51,836
[ Indistinct talking ]

267
00:12:56,008 --> 00:12:58,309
[ Talking continues ]

268
00:13:01,980 --> 00:13:03,547
Mrs. Burton.

269
00:13:03,549 --> 00:13:05,716
I think you'll find
Richard's in wardrobe.

270
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:07,051
Over this way.
Oh, thank you.

271
00:13:16,695 --> 00:13:19,530
So, you have plans
for dinner tonight?

272
00:13:19,532 --> 00:13:21,932
Well, I thought
we'd go somewhere quiet.

273
00:13:21,934 --> 00:13:23,034
"We"?

274
00:13:23,036 --> 00:13:24,935
"Us," stupid.

275
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:26,003
Oh.

276
00:13:26,005 --> 00:13:27,038
[ Chuckles ]

277
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,406
Whatever you say, dumpy.

278
00:13:28,408 --> 00:13:29,940
[ Chuckles softly ]

279
00:13:29,942 --> 00:13:30,941
Oh!

280
00:13:30,943 --> 00:13:32,943
[ Indistinct shouting ]

281
00:13:47,492 --> 00:13:48,826
What the hell is this?

282
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:50,394
Mr. Zanuck,
let me be clear --

283
00:13:50,396 --> 00:13:51,429
our department had nothing to do
with these photographs.

284
00:13:51,431 --> 00:13:52,830
Who in the hell shot this?

285
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:54,565
Well, it's just kids
on motor scooters.

286
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:57,001
Rome is infested with them.
They call them "paparazzi."

287
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:58,336
"Paparazzi"?

288
00:13:58,338 --> 00:13:59,637
It means
"little buzzing insects."

289
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:01,038
I-I think Fellini
actually coined the word.

290
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,473
Like I care.

291
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:05,443
I have a publicity department
<i>precisely</i>

292
00:14:05,445 --> 00:14:10,481
so that photos like these
do not, not, <i>not</i> get published.

293
00:14:10,483 --> 00:14:11,816
Capiche?

294
00:14:11,818 --> 00:14:12,850
Yes, sir.

295
00:14:12,852 --> 00:14:14,785
- Fix it.
- Yes, sir.

296
00:14:14,787 --> 00:14:16,754
This was <i>the</i> scandal.

297
00:14:16,756 --> 00:14:18,756
It wasn't just
that we were having an affair.

298
00:14:18,758 --> 00:14:21,092
No, movie stars had affairs
all the time.

299
00:14:21,094 --> 00:14:23,861
Before us, they never really wrote
about affairs between married people.

300
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:28,466
And, of course, we were married,
and we had children.

301
00:14:28,468 --> 00:14:30,568
[ Laughing ]
I was the monster

302
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:32,603
that broke up
America's sweethearts.

303
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:34,772
She's talking about Eddie fisher
and Debbie Reynolds.

304
00:14:34,774 --> 00:14:36,607
They know
who I'm talking about, Richard.

305
00:14:36,609 --> 00:14:38,142
And, of course,
Eddie had been best man

306
00:14:38,144 --> 00:14:40,378
at Mike Todd's wedding,
so...

307
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:41,846
So shoot me.

308
00:14:41,848 --> 00:14:44,515
Do I sound defensive?
Because I'm not.

309
00:14:44,517 --> 00:14:47,551
Eddie chased me, and I was
stupid enough to give in.

310
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:48,953
Yes.

311
00:14:48,955 --> 00:14:51,088
And you were vulnerable
after Mike's death.

312
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:53,424
Besides...

313
00:14:53,426 --> 00:14:56,093
How were you to know
that <i>I</i> was going to come along?

314
00:14:56,095 --> 00:14:58,028
[ Laughs ]

315
00:14:58,030 --> 00:15:01,132
Like you had any idea of what
was going to hit <i>you,</i> Buster.

316
00:15:01,134 --> 00:15:03,901
With <i>her?!</i>

317
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:05,169
You think I'll stay

318
00:15:05,171 --> 00:15:07,171
and have this pushed in my face
every day?

319
00:15:07,173 --> 00:15:08,172
But, Sybil --

320
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:09,607
Don't!

321
00:15:09,609 --> 00:15:11,776
No more lies!

322
00:15:13,178 --> 00:15:17,047
I've put up with years
of your wandering.

323
00:15:17,049 --> 00:15:20,584
But at least you didn't
make a fool of me in public.

324
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:23,854
I look at these
and can only imagine

325
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:26,557
you think
I'm a worthless idiot!

326
00:15:29,928 --> 00:15:33,197
[ Paparazzi shouting ]

327
00:15:34,933 --> 00:15:36,967
Have you heard
about the news, Eddie?!

328
00:15:36,969 --> 00:15:38,669
I went to New York
to do a show.

329
00:15:38,671 --> 00:15:40,204
Now I'm back
to see my wife.

330
00:15:40,206 --> 00:15:42,173
Have you seen the pictures
in the paper, Eddie?!

331
00:15:42,175 --> 00:15:43,507
Guys...

332
00:15:43,509 --> 00:15:44,508
What about pictures?!

333
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,876
...forget about it, huh?

334
00:15:45,878 --> 00:15:47,511
You never seen
publicity?

335
00:15:47,513 --> 00:15:50,514
[ Indistinct shouting ]

336
00:15:50,516 --> 00:15:53,150
[ Indistinct talking ]

337
00:15:53,152 --> 00:15:54,585
You would!

338
00:15:55,754 --> 00:15:57,822
No, don't, don't.
No, no, please.

339
00:15:57,824 --> 00:16:00,090
Hold your liquor.
Hold your liquor.

340
00:16:00,092 --> 00:16:01,525
Eddie!

341
00:16:01,527 --> 00:16:04,028
The prodigal returns.

342
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,095
Come.

343
00:16:05,097 --> 00:16:07,465
Sit.
Have a drink.

344
00:16:08,166 --> 00:16:09,000
Here.

345
00:16:09,002 --> 00:16:10,668
We've just been
talking about you.

346
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:11,703
What are you doing here?

347
00:16:11,705 --> 00:16:12,537
Oh, I'm sleeping
with your wife.

348
00:16:12,539 --> 00:16:13,638
What'd you say?

349
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:15,673
Yes, it's been
in all the papers.

350
00:16:15,675 --> 00:16:16,574
I'm sleeping
with Elizabeth.

351
00:16:16,576 --> 00:16:17,575
Liz?

352
00:16:17,577 --> 00:16:18,976
Ed...

353
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:20,744
In fact, Eddie,
I'm glad you're here,

354
00:16:20,746 --> 00:16:23,714
because I have a question
for Elizabeth,

355
00:16:23,716 --> 00:16:26,784
and --
and it does concern <i>you.</i>

356
00:16:26,786 --> 00:16:30,020
Dear Elizabeth,
Queen of the Nile,

357
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:32,690
here we both are, two schoolboys
begging for your hand,

358
00:16:32,692 --> 00:16:34,258
and my question to you
is this...

359
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:36,126
Who do you love --
him or me?

360
00:16:36,128 --> 00:16:37,995
- What are you doing here?
- Richard.

361
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,730
No, serious question.
It deserves a serious answer.

362
00:16:39,732 --> 00:16:42,132
So, Elizabeth,
answer us now.

363
00:16:42,134 --> 00:16:44,602
Who do you love --
Eddie or me?

364
00:16:44,604 --> 00:16:46,604
I can't hear you,
Elizabeth!

365
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:48,739
Who do you love --
Me or Eddie?!

366
00:16:48,741 --> 00:16:50,608
[ Sighs ]

367
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:51,809
You.

368
00:16:51,811 --> 00:16:54,178
A little louder, please,
for the room.

369
00:16:57,249 --> 00:16:58,516
I love <i>you.</i>

370
00:17:00,151 --> 00:17:02,286
[ Sighs ]

371
00:17:02,288 --> 00:17:04,889
[ People murmuring ]

372
00:17:07,092 --> 00:17:09,293
Sara: Elizabeth!

373
00:17:09,295 --> 00:17:12,162
Elizabeth,
not that I'm counting,

374
00:17:12,164 --> 00:17:13,597
but if I'm not mistaken,

375
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,566
you just ended -- what --
your fourth marriage?

376
00:17:15,568 --> 00:17:16,901
Who's counting?

377
00:17:16,903 --> 00:17:19,103
It might be a record
for a 29-year-old.

378
00:17:19,105 --> 00:17:21,639
What am I
supposed to do?

379
00:17:21,641 --> 00:17:24,608
I love the man --
end of story.

380
00:17:27,147 --> 00:17:29,080
And cut.

381
00:17:29,082 --> 00:17:31,149
All right, places, please.

382
00:17:32,151 --> 00:17:34,285
All right, then,
I think we can --

383
00:17:34,287 --> 00:17:36,020
where...

384
00:17:36,022 --> 00:17:37,555
Woman:
Miss Taylor.

385
00:17:37,557 --> 00:17:38,756
You let them leave?

386
00:17:38,758 --> 00:17:41,058
[ Tires squeal ]

387
00:18:04,616 --> 00:18:08,786
"His flashing eyes,
his floating hair.

388
00:18:08,788 --> 00:18:11,622
"Weave a circle
round him thrice,

389
00:18:11,624 --> 00:18:14,658
"and close your eyes
with holy dread.

390
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:18,228
"For he on honeydew
hath fed

391
00:18:18,230 --> 00:18:22,366
and drunk
the milk of paradise."

392
00:18:26,805 --> 00:18:29,273
Who knew
Italy could be so hot?

393
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:33,677
[ Sighs ]

394
00:18:33,679 --> 00:18:35,179
Last one upstairs
is a goof.

395
00:18:35,181 --> 00:18:36,780
Goof? What kind of a word
is "goof"?

396
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,682
I can see we're gonna have to
teach Miss Taylor

397
00:18:38,684 --> 00:18:41,385
some better English!

398
00:18:45,991 --> 00:18:47,758
We could go
to the pool.

399
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:51,295
I don't need a pool.
I've got a whole ocean in <i>you.</i>

400
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:57,234
[ Chuckles ]

401
00:18:57,236 --> 00:18:59,370
"License my roving hands.

402
00:18:59,372 --> 00:19:01,739
"Let them go...

403
00:19:01,741 --> 00:19:07,077
"Before, behind,
between, above, below.

404
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:12,650
"Oh, my America,
my new-found-land, my kingdom,

405
00:19:12,652 --> 00:19:16,854
safeliest
when with one man manned."

406
00:19:16,856 --> 00:19:18,255
[ Sighs ]

407
00:19:18,257 --> 00:19:20,124
More!

408
00:19:20,126 --> 00:19:21,225
I want more.

409
00:19:21,227 --> 00:19:22,793
"More."

410
00:19:22,795 --> 00:19:25,329
I'm starting to feel
that may be your favorite word.

411
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:26,730
[ Laughs ]

412
00:19:26,732 --> 00:19:29,133
Would you prefer "less"?

413
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,269
[ Laughs ]

414
00:19:32,271 --> 00:19:33,337
No.

415
00:19:33,339 --> 00:19:34,405
[ Laughs ]

416
00:19:34,407 --> 00:19:36,840
[ Sighs ]

417
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:45,783
No electricity,

418
00:19:45,785 --> 00:19:48,452
and it's as moldy
as a rugby player's sock.

419
00:19:48,454 --> 00:19:52,356
- Yes, but it's ours, which
makes it perfect. - Perfect.

420
00:19:52,358 --> 00:19:54,792
[ Laughs ]

421
00:20:10,775 --> 00:20:12,276
Miss Taylor!

422
00:20:12,278 --> 00:20:14,378
[ Indistinct shouting ]

423
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:19,783
Turn this way, please!

424
00:20:19,785 --> 00:20:21,251
Look over here, please!

425
00:20:21,253 --> 00:20:23,120
You call yourselves
journalists?!

426
00:20:23,122 --> 00:20:25,122
Why the hell do you want
more photographs of us?!

427
00:20:25,124 --> 00:20:26,924
Elizabeth,
come on inside!

428
00:20:26,926 --> 00:20:29,293
One picture, please.
Please!

429
00:20:29,295 --> 00:20:31,328
[ Indistinct talking ]

430
00:20:33,898 --> 00:20:36,900
[ Laughing ]

431
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:38,202
You flashed them
your bum.

432
00:20:38,204 --> 00:20:40,738
We'll see if they'll run that.
I don't think so.

433
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,272
Are you kidding me?

434
00:20:42,274 --> 00:20:43,807
That's going to be the most
popular postcard in Rome.

435
00:20:43,809 --> 00:20:45,209
[ Laughing ] No.

436
00:20:45,211 --> 00:20:47,411
Miss Taylor's derrière,
sir. Mmm.

437
00:20:47,413 --> 00:20:48,812
Screw it.

438
00:20:48,814 --> 00:20:51,215
They want a show,
let's give them a show.

439
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:02,760
[ Indistinct shouting ]

440
00:21:16,808 --> 00:21:19,543
[ Bells jingle ]

441
00:21:19,545 --> 00:21:21,845
Signora Taylor.

442
00:21:21,847 --> 00:21:24,481
Wow!
Que bellissima.

443
00:21:24,483 --> 00:21:25,883
Come va?

444
00:21:25,885 --> 00:21:28,352
- Ah, Signor Burton.
- Gianni.

445
00:21:28,354 --> 00:21:29,920
[ Speaking Italian ]

446
00:21:29,922 --> 00:21:32,389
What can I
help you with?

447
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:33,390
Hmm.

448
00:21:33,392 --> 00:21:35,459
Richard...

449
00:21:35,461 --> 00:21:37,461
Look how beautiful.

450
00:21:39,130 --> 00:21:42,800
Well,
since we're here...

451
00:21:42,802 --> 00:21:45,469
Really?
Can I choose something?

452
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:47,471
Anything you like.

453
00:21:47,473 --> 00:21:49,273
Anything?

454
00:21:49,275 --> 00:21:53,510
For you, Elizabeth,
anything.

455
00:21:53,512 --> 00:21:55,345
[ Sighs ]

456
00:21:59,484 --> 00:22:01,385
[ Laughs ]

457
00:22:03,421 --> 00:22:05,422
[ Chuckles ]

458
00:22:11,596 --> 00:22:13,363
Oh.

459
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:17,601
[ Gasps ]

460
00:22:17,603 --> 00:22:18,936
Thank you, Gianni.

461
00:22:18,938 --> 00:22:20,571
Niente.

462
00:22:20,573 --> 00:22:22,339
<i>I'm</i> the one you should
be thanking, not him.

463
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:23,307
Thank you.

464
00:22:23,309 --> 00:22:24,541
[ Laughing ]
Thank you.

465
00:22:24,543 --> 00:22:26,210
Elizabeth:
It's always about the jewels.

466
00:22:26,212 --> 00:22:28,378
Men just don't realize it
till it's too late

467
00:22:28,380 --> 00:22:29,413
and we have them all.

468
00:22:29,415 --> 00:22:30,514
[ Laughs ]

469
00:22:30,516 --> 00:22:32,482
[ Laughs ]

470
00:22:32,484 --> 00:22:34,618
[ Chuckles ]

471
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:37,187
[ Indistinct shouting ]

472
00:22:39,324 --> 00:22:42,626
Signor Burton, your wife
attempted suicide, yes?

473
00:22:42,628 --> 00:22:43,894
What did you say?

474
00:22:43,896 --> 00:22:46,363
Suicide, yes!

475
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:47,931
Elizabeth,
I'm sorry.

476
00:22:47,933 --> 00:22:49,600
I have to go
to Sybil.

477
00:22:49,602 --> 00:22:51,368
[ Shouting continues ]

478
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:53,503
Know why she did it?

479
00:22:54,372 --> 00:22:55,906
- Mr. Burton?
- You know I love you.

480
00:22:55,908 --> 00:22:59,576
Mr. Burton,
were you having some problems?

481
00:22:59,578 --> 00:23:01,011
[ Speaking Italian ]

482
00:23:01,013 --> 00:23:02,246
Why did she do it?

483
00:23:02,248 --> 00:23:03,380
Where are you
going now?

484
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:06,950
Katie.

485
00:23:06,952 --> 00:23:10,587
[ Sighs ]

486
00:23:10,589 --> 00:23:12,022
Off to bed.

487
00:23:13,625 --> 00:23:16,093
Where were you?

488
00:23:16,095 --> 00:23:18,061
Lost in the middle
of an ocean.

489
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:19,630
"Lost in the middle
of an ocean"?

490
00:23:19,632 --> 00:23:21,632
What kind of poeting bollocks
is that?

491
00:23:21,634 --> 00:23:23,667
You have a family here
that's drowning!

492
00:23:23,669 --> 00:23:25,636
I love Elizabeth.

493
00:23:25,638 --> 00:23:28,505
Tough.
You're already taken.

494
00:23:28,507 --> 00:23:30,107
We were meant
for each other.

495
00:23:30,109 --> 00:23:32,409
That's what she said
to Conrad Hilton,

496
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:35,479
Michael Wilding, Mike Todd,
and Eddie bloody Fisher.

497
00:23:35,481 --> 00:23:39,182
Look around you, man.
This is your family.

498
00:23:43,388 --> 00:23:46,023
[ Birds chirping ]

499
00:23:48,092 --> 00:23:51,395
[ Door opens ]

500
00:23:51,397 --> 00:23:53,397
[ Footsteps approaching ]

501
00:23:54,699 --> 00:23:57,000
Well, she's alive.

502
00:23:57,002 --> 00:23:59,136
But I fear <i>I</i> am dead.

503
00:23:59,138 --> 00:24:00,671
I can't.

504
00:24:00,673 --> 00:24:03,140
I'm sorry,
but it's as simple as that.

505
00:24:03,142 --> 00:24:04,441
I can't.

506
00:24:04,443 --> 00:24:07,344
[ Breathing shakily ]

507
00:24:07,346 --> 00:24:08,445
[ Exhales sharply ]

508
00:24:08,447 --> 00:24:10,147
I won't live
without you!

509
00:24:10,149 --> 00:24:12,449
Elizabeth!

510
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:15,185
[ Crying ]

511
00:24:19,691 --> 00:24:20,691
Elizabeth?

512
00:24:20,693 --> 00:24:22,059
[ Sniffles ]

513
00:24:23,728 --> 00:24:24,728
Elizabeth!

514
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:27,464
[ Crying ]

515
00:24:31,069 --> 00:24:32,402
[ Crying ]
You can go.

516
00:24:32,404 --> 00:24:33,603
[ Sniffles ]

517
00:24:33,605 --> 00:24:35,439
This shouldn't take
too long.

518
00:24:35,441 --> 00:24:37,007
Don't talk like that.

519
00:24:37,009 --> 00:24:39,409
You know I can't turn my back
on my responsibilities.

520
00:24:39,411 --> 00:24:40,444
[ Sniffles ]

521
00:24:40,446 --> 00:24:42,512
That's why
I'm removing myself.

522
00:24:42,514 --> 00:24:44,648
I don't want to be
your responsibility.

523
00:24:44,650 --> 00:24:46,683
Don't.

524
00:24:46,685 --> 00:24:48,051
[ Sniffles ]

525
00:24:48,053 --> 00:24:50,420
I already have.

526
00:24:50,422 --> 00:24:51,555
[ Crying ]

527
00:24:51,557 --> 00:24:52,589
Elizabeth?

528
00:24:52,591 --> 00:24:55,459
[ Crying ]
I already have.

529
00:24:57,462 --> 00:24:58,996
How many were in here?

530
00:24:58,998 --> 00:25:01,131
Elizabeth,
how many did you take?

531
00:25:01,133 --> 00:25:03,066
[ Crying ]

532
00:25:03,068 --> 00:25:04,568
[ Sniffles ]

533
00:25:04,570 --> 00:25:06,003
All.
All of them.

534
00:25:06,005 --> 00:25:07,637
Come here. Come here.

535
00:25:07,639 --> 00:25:08,739
[ Moans ]

536
00:25:08,741 --> 00:25:10,140
Come here, now.

537
00:25:10,142 --> 00:25:11,675
[ Crying ]

538
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:13,243
Come here.

539
00:25:15,747 --> 00:25:18,081
[ Woman speaking Italian
over P.A.]

540
00:25:18,083 --> 00:25:19,116
Help me!

541
00:25:19,118 --> 00:25:21,184
[ Doctors speaking Italian ]

542
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:23,020
Somebody,
please help me!

543
00:25:23,022 --> 00:25:25,122
[ Speaking Italian ]

544
00:25:27,091 --> 00:25:29,092
[ Groans ]

545
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:38,301
[ Woman speaking Italian
over P.A. ]

546
00:25:38,303 --> 00:25:41,738
Mr. Burton,
she will be fine.

547
00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:45,575
But she does not want
to see you.

548
00:25:59,257 --> 00:26:02,559
Joe:
How you doing?

549
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:04,461
Almost ready.

550
00:26:04,463 --> 00:26:07,631
That's...
Not what I was asking.

551
00:26:09,467 --> 00:26:13,103
Only one more scene,
and we're done.

552
00:26:14,172 --> 00:26:15,205
Joe.

553
00:26:15,207 --> 00:26:16,840
Mm-hmm?

554
00:26:16,842 --> 00:26:18,341
When you wrote this,

555
00:26:18,343 --> 00:26:21,678
were you thinking
about Antony and Cleopatra

556
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,113
or me and Richard?

557
00:26:23,115 --> 00:26:25,615
Antony and Cleopatra,
of course.

558
00:26:25,617 --> 00:26:27,484
Of course.

559
00:26:32,223 --> 00:26:35,859
What happened to you?

560
00:26:35,861 --> 00:26:37,661
<i>You</i> did.

561
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:44,134
Joe: And cut!

562
00:26:44,136 --> 00:26:46,236
And that's a wrap.

563
00:26:46,238 --> 00:26:48,205
[ Cheers and applause ]

564
00:26:50,108 --> 00:26:51,541
Man: All right!

565
00:26:51,543 --> 00:26:53,176
Woman:
Oh, my God, we did it!

566
00:26:53,178 --> 00:26:55,145
Thank you, thank you, thank you,
thank you, thank you!

567
00:26:55,147 --> 00:26:56,646
Just so happy.

568
00:26:56,648 --> 00:26:58,215
[ Indistinct conversations ]

569
00:26:58,217 --> 00:26:59,549
Lovely.
Brilliant.

570
00:26:59,551 --> 00:27:00,851
It's brilliant.
Mwah!

571
00:27:00,853 --> 00:27:03,820
Such a -- mwah! --
Brilliant movie.

572
00:27:07,358 --> 00:27:09,659
Will you give us
a minute?

573
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:19,336
Do you have
anything lined up?

574
00:27:19,338 --> 00:27:22,172
[ Sighs ]

575
00:27:22,174 --> 00:27:25,842
I think I need a break --
a <i>long</i> break.

576
00:27:25,844 --> 00:27:27,844
Me too.

577
00:27:30,114 --> 00:27:31,148
And?

578
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:32,849
You mean Sybil.

579
00:27:35,386 --> 00:27:37,621
It will be hard,
but she's agreed to try again.

580
00:27:38,123 --> 00:27:40,357
Elizabeth,
you already knew that.

581
00:27:40,359 --> 00:27:42,826
So you've come to rub my face
in it, then, have you?

582
00:27:42,828 --> 00:27:44,594
[ Sighs ]

583
00:27:44,596 --> 00:27:46,830
It's for the children,
Elizabeth.

584
00:27:46,832 --> 00:27:48,899
I can't do it
to the children.

585
00:27:48,901 --> 00:27:50,267
[ Sniffles ]

586
00:27:50,269 --> 00:27:52,235
You knew you could never
leave them!

587
00:27:52,237 --> 00:27:53,370
You <i>were</i> playing!

588
00:27:53,372 --> 00:27:55,438
I <i>was</i> just another notch!

589
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:58,275
Damn it! How dare you
speak to me like that!

590
00:27:58,277 --> 00:28:02,279
My heart is broken,
and <i>you</i> have the smashed pieces!

591
00:28:02,281 --> 00:28:04,447
Please...

592
00:28:04,449 --> 00:28:06,750
Please,
don't make this any harder.

593
00:28:10,221 --> 00:28:11,454
Have you spoken
with Eddie?

594
00:28:11,456 --> 00:28:13,723
I have no reason
to speak to Eddie!

595
00:28:17,962 --> 00:28:19,696
[ Inhales sharply ]

596
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:22,866
You look at me
like you loathe me.

597
00:28:22,868 --> 00:28:26,269
[ Exhales sharply ]

598
00:28:26,271 --> 00:28:28,205
I don't loathe you.

599
00:28:28,207 --> 00:28:30,273
I <i>hate</i> you!

600
00:28:33,477 --> 00:28:35,845
No.

601
00:28:35,847 --> 00:28:36,947
No.

602
00:28:36,949 --> 00:28:38,215
[ Sniffles ]

603
00:28:38,217 --> 00:28:39,282
No, you don't.

604
00:28:39,284 --> 00:28:40,383
[ Voice breaking ] No.

605
00:28:40,385 --> 00:28:41,952
I don't.

606
00:28:43,955 --> 00:28:46,289
[ Crying ]

607
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:52,929
[ Door opens ]

608
00:28:52,931 --> 00:28:53,930
[ Door closes ]

609
00:28:53,932 --> 00:28:55,232
[ Exhales sharply ]

610
00:28:59,470 --> 00:29:01,938
[ Birds chirping ]

611
00:29:11,749 --> 00:29:14,451
Mom, mom!
Come play piggy in the middle.

612
00:29:14,453 --> 00:29:16,019
What's
piggy in the middle?

613
00:29:16,021 --> 00:29:17,020
[ Both laugh ]

614
00:29:17,022 --> 00:29:18,255
Never mind.

615
00:29:18,257 --> 00:29:20,290
[ Both laugh ]

616
00:29:26,964 --> 00:29:28,965
[ Sighs ]

617
00:29:28,967 --> 00:29:31,868
[ Sighs ]

618
00:29:31,870 --> 00:29:34,771
[ Sighs ]

619
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:36,273
I'm bored!

620
00:29:36,275 --> 00:29:37,974
I'm so bored!

621
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:39,809
[ Sighs ]

622
00:29:45,283 --> 00:29:47,484
What? I'm bored.

623
00:29:47,486 --> 00:29:49,486
Hell, what do people do
when they aren't working?

624
00:29:49,488 --> 00:29:51,821
Don't ask them, dear.
They <i>are</i> working.

625
00:29:51,823 --> 00:29:53,923
Of course they are.
What am <i>I</i> supposed to do?

626
00:29:53,925 --> 00:29:57,327
I've done 29 pictures
since I was 9.

627
00:29:57,329 --> 00:29:58,828
29!

628
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:00,830
I've never learned how to do
just absolutely nothing!

629
00:30:00,832 --> 00:30:03,633
I don't even know
how to play these games.

630
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:05,869
[ Sighs ] Would you like
to go for a drive?

631
00:30:09,573 --> 00:30:11,074
Perhaps you'd like
to read <i>this.</i>

632
00:30:11,076 --> 00:30:12,008
A fan letter?

633
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:13,343
Sort of.

634
00:30:13,345 --> 00:30:14,577
It's from Richard.

635
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:17,414
When did that come?

636
00:30:17,416 --> 00:30:20,083
Two days ago.
It was posted in Celigny.

637
00:30:20,085 --> 00:30:21,718
I didn't know
he was here.

638
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,453
You said
you didn't want me to --

639
00:30:23,455 --> 00:30:25,989
Well, I <i>do</i> want.

640
00:30:25,991 --> 00:30:27,357
I do.

641
00:30:27,359 --> 00:30:29,025
Could I have some privacy,
please?

642
00:30:29,027 --> 00:30:31,061
Of course.

643
00:30:34,031 --> 00:30:37,067
[ Sighs ]

644
00:30:37,069 --> 00:30:39,336
[ Sighs ]

645
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:50,914
[ Sighs ]

646
00:30:52,616 --> 00:30:54,918
[ Sighs ]

647
00:30:55,986 --> 00:30:58,054
Shall I wait?

648
00:30:58,056 --> 00:30:59,456
No, it's okay.

649
00:30:59,458 --> 00:31:01,458
You could come back
in a few hours.

650
00:31:01,460 --> 00:31:02,959
Okay, sweetie.

651
00:31:02,961 --> 00:31:05,095
[ Indistinct conversations ]

652
00:31:15,539 --> 00:31:17,474
Richard.

653
00:31:17,476 --> 00:31:18,908
You look wonderful.

654
00:31:19,910 --> 00:31:21,878
Don't say anything.
I know I look terrible.

655
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,480
Please -- sit.

656
00:31:25,516 --> 00:31:26,783
Can I get you anything?

657
00:31:26,785 --> 00:31:28,918
Uh, uh, coffee,
hot chocolate, tea?

658
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:31,388
A cappuccino would be nice,
please.

659
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:32,655
Cappuccino.
Thank you.

660
00:31:41,499 --> 00:31:44,067
So, how are
your children?

661
00:31:44,069 --> 00:31:46,503
Um, bored with me.

662
00:31:46,505 --> 00:31:48,104
How's <i>your</i> family?

663
00:31:48,106 --> 00:31:49,939
Uh...

664
00:31:49,941 --> 00:31:52,509
Ifor's fine.

665
00:31:52,511 --> 00:31:56,146
Uh, the rest
of the siblings -- good.

666
00:31:56,148 --> 00:31:57,514
But, um...

667
00:31:57,516 --> 00:31:58,982
I'm in hell.

668
00:32:00,951 --> 00:32:01,985
[ Chuckles ]

669
00:32:01,987 --> 00:32:04,454
"Hell" is
as good a word as any.

670
00:32:07,558 --> 00:32:10,593
Thank you for coming.
I didn't know if you would.

671
00:32:12,863 --> 00:32:14,564
Tell me,
will this pass?

672
00:32:14,566 --> 00:32:16,533
Because it doesn't feel
that it will.

673
00:32:17,235 --> 00:32:19,903
I don't know.

674
00:32:19,905 --> 00:32:21,771
Damned if I know.

675
00:32:25,176 --> 00:32:26,443
Thank you.

676
00:32:38,522 --> 00:32:39,889
[ Sighs ]

677
00:32:39,891 --> 00:32:42,125
So, tell me --
are you gonna see him again?

678
00:32:42,427 --> 00:32:44,861
Maybe.

679
00:33:08,953 --> 00:33:11,254
[ Door closes ]

680
00:33:11,256 --> 00:33:12,655
I'm so sorry I'm late.

681
00:33:12,657 --> 00:33:14,757
Oh, don't be silly.
Of course you're not.

682
00:33:14,759 --> 00:33:15,758
[ Chuckles ]

683
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:16,993
Drink?

684
00:33:16,995 --> 00:33:18,728
Yes, please.

685
00:33:18,730 --> 00:33:20,163
I...

686
00:33:20,165 --> 00:33:22,031
I brought you a gift.

687
00:33:22,533 --> 00:33:25,034
And I have one for <i>you.</i>

688
00:33:29,273 --> 00:33:30,673
John Donne.

689
00:33:34,178 --> 00:33:36,513
The 1635 edition?

690
00:33:36,515 --> 00:33:39,048
This must've cost you
a fortune.

691
00:33:40,584 --> 00:33:43,186
A million thank-yous.

692
00:33:45,589 --> 00:33:47,657
Now, my gift
is not nearly good enough.

693
00:33:47,659 --> 00:33:50,660
Oh, stop it.
That's not the point.

694
00:33:50,662 --> 00:33:52,795
Well,
it's English country gardens.

695
00:33:52,797 --> 00:33:54,931
I remember you said
you missed them.

696
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,667
Thank you.

697
00:33:57,669 --> 00:34:00,069
That's very thoughtful.

698
00:34:00,071 --> 00:34:02,872
I'll enjoy this.

699
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:05,074
I've enjoyed not filming,
as well.

700
00:34:05,076 --> 00:34:08,111
I'm not sure
I want to go back -- ever.

701
00:34:08,113 --> 00:34:10,079
[ Chuckles ]

702
00:34:10,581 --> 00:34:11,714
What?

703
00:34:13,651 --> 00:34:15,251
I <i>have</i> taken a film.

704
00:34:16,555 --> 00:34:20,256
Well I had to...
I couldn't sit around here doing <i>this.</i>

705
00:34:20,258 --> 00:34:23,593
They'd find me
floating facedown in a lake.

706
00:34:23,595 --> 00:34:24,861
What film? Where?

707
00:34:25,363 --> 00:34:29,098
London, uh, "The V.I.P.s" --
silly title, really.

708
00:34:29,100 --> 00:34:31,801
I play a rich man whose wife
is running around on him.

709
00:34:31,803 --> 00:34:33,236
Perfect role for me,
though.

710
00:34:33,238 --> 00:34:35,738
I get to sit around
looking all gloomy

711
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:37,574
and drink
like a proverbial fish.

712
00:34:37,576 --> 00:34:38,741
Method acting.

713
00:34:38,743 --> 00:34:40,977
[ Chuckles ]

714
00:34:40,979 --> 00:34:42,979
Who's going to play
the lucky wife?

715
00:34:42,981 --> 00:34:45,281
The producers
want Sophia Loren.

716
00:34:45,283 --> 00:34:48,117
Hmm. Do they, now?

717
00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:50,887
Richard Burton
and Sophia Loren.

718
00:34:50,889 --> 00:34:52,855
I think la Loren
should stay in Rome.

719
00:34:52,857 --> 00:34:54,757
[ Book thuds ]

720
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:56,793
Well, you heard me.

721
00:34:56,795 --> 00:34:58,828
That role is <i>mine.</i>

722
00:35:01,601 --> 00:35:02,600
But Miss Taylor,

723
00:35:02,601 --> 00:35:05,802
we couldn't afford you
even if I wanted you,

724
00:35:05,804 --> 00:35:07,270
and I <i>don't</i> want you.

725
00:35:07,272 --> 00:35:08,371
Do you want people
to see the picture?

726
00:35:08,373 --> 00:35:09,906
Of course.

727
00:35:09,908 --> 00:35:11,307
Well, then,
you'll want publicity,

728
00:35:11,309 --> 00:35:12,909
and trust me --
Taylor/Burton brings publicity.

729
00:35:12,911 --> 00:35:14,711
Maybe that's not
the kind of publicity I want.

730
00:35:14,713 --> 00:35:15,979
Then you're a fool.

731
00:35:15,981 --> 00:35:18,381
You pay me and fire
all of your P.R. people,

732
00:35:18,383 --> 00:35:20,316
because, buddy,
you won't need them.

733
00:35:20,318 --> 00:35:21,884
You'll save money
and have a huge hit.

734
00:35:21,886 --> 00:35:23,786
I'm sorry, but no.

735
00:35:23,788 --> 00:35:25,822
[ Receiver slams ]

736
00:35:25,824 --> 00:35:29,359
I'm not hiring
Elizabeth Taylor!

737
00:35:31,662 --> 00:35:33,396
Your suite,
Miss Taylor.

738
00:35:33,398 --> 00:35:35,131
Thank you.

739
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:36,399
[ Knock on door ]

740
00:35:36,401 --> 00:35:37,900
What's that?

741
00:35:37,902 --> 00:35:40,803
Uh, that would be
to the adjoining suite.

742
00:35:40,805 --> 00:35:41,804
[ Gasps ]

743
00:35:41,806 --> 00:35:42,872
Hello, lumpy.

744
00:35:42,874 --> 00:35:44,240
[ Laughs ]

745
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:48,711
Man: There you are.
Enjoy your evening.

746
00:35:48,713 --> 00:35:49,679
Woman: Thank you.

747
00:35:49,681 --> 00:35:50,780
Very welcome.

748
00:35:50,782 --> 00:35:53,149
[ Telephone ringing ]

749
00:35:53,151 --> 00:35:56,386
[ Ringing continues ]

750
00:35:59,290 --> 00:36:02,759
Oh, God! That's the seventh time
it's rung!

751
00:36:02,761 --> 00:36:04,661
You know it's Sybil.
Where is she?

752
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:07,730
[ Ringing stops ]
Our house, North London.

753
00:36:07,732 --> 00:36:11,434
I told her I needed to be
near the film, which means <i>you.</i>

754
00:36:11,436 --> 00:36:13,903
[ Laughs ]

755
00:36:18,776 --> 00:36:20,443
[ Ringing resumes ]

756
00:36:20,445 --> 00:36:21,878
Oh, hell's bells!

757
00:36:23,247 --> 00:36:25,381
All right,
I've had enough!

758
00:36:25,383 --> 00:36:26,849
What are you doing?

759
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:28,451
I'm going over there <i>now.</i>

760
00:36:28,453 --> 00:36:30,353
I want a divorce!

761
00:36:30,355 --> 00:36:31,320
Damn it!

762
00:36:31,322 --> 00:36:33,356
Well, hurry back.

763
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:34,991
I want more.

764
00:36:34,993 --> 00:36:36,459
I want more.

765
00:36:36,461 --> 00:36:37,460
[ Laughs ]

766
00:36:37,462 --> 00:36:39,095
[ Chuckles ]

767
00:36:41,799 --> 00:36:43,900
[ Tires screeching ]

768
00:36:54,344 --> 00:36:55,878
Sybil!

769
00:36:58,415 --> 00:36:59,482
Sybil!

770
00:36:59,484 --> 00:37:01,384
[ Groans ]

771
00:37:01,386 --> 00:37:02,819
Richard.

772
00:37:02,821 --> 00:37:04,153
- Richard.
- Ifor.

773
00:37:04,155 --> 00:37:06,022
I wondered when
you'd finally come home.

774
00:37:06,024 --> 00:37:07,423
I've been calling
the hotel.

775
00:37:07,425 --> 00:37:09,025
I didn't realize
you were here.

776
00:37:09,027 --> 00:37:10,460
I've come
to speak to Sybil.

777
00:37:10,462 --> 00:37:12,795
She's asleep. Why don't you
talk to <i>me</i> instead?

778
00:37:12,797 --> 00:37:14,297
Fine.

779
00:37:14,299 --> 00:37:16,466
Look at the state of you,
acting like a teenager.

780
00:37:16,468 --> 00:37:18,901
"Oh, I love her.
Oh, she was meant for me."

781
00:37:18,903 --> 00:37:21,404
Don't you talk to me
about Elizabeth <i>ever.</i>

782
00:37:21,406 --> 00:37:23,973
- All right, let's talk about <i>you.</i>
<i>- Fine.</i>

783
00:37:23,975 --> 00:37:26,442
An affair born in betrayal
will end in ashes.

784
00:37:26,444 --> 00:37:28,778
Oh, Ifor,
we're not in chapel now.

785
00:37:28,780 --> 00:37:29,912
This is real life.

786
00:37:29,914 --> 00:37:31,948
Let me tell you
what real life is --

787
00:37:31,950 --> 00:37:33,783
family, loyalty,
commitment.

788
00:37:33,785 --> 00:37:35,384
You think
I don't know that?

789
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:37,954
Then behave like you do
and act like a bloody grown-up!

790
00:37:39,389 --> 00:37:42,058
[ Sighs ]

791
00:37:42,060 --> 00:37:43,526
Right.

792
00:37:43,528 --> 00:37:45,795
[ Engine shuts off ]

793
00:37:45,797 --> 00:37:47,196
[ Sighs ] Get in.

794
00:37:53,937 --> 00:37:57,373
[ Sighs ]

