make a dime off of me

1056
00:49:32,536 --> 00:49:34,002
after we've divorced.

1057
00:49:39,609 --> 00:49:41,143
[ Elevator bell dings ]

1058
00:49:41,145 --> 00:49:42,478
Hi.

1059
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:44,513
Um, we have a reservation
under "Smith."

1060
00:49:44,515 --> 00:49:46,148
Hmm.

1061
00:49:46,150 --> 00:49:48,484
Here you are,
Mademoiselle Smith.

1062
00:49:48,486 --> 00:49:49,618
Thank you, sir.

1063
00:49:49,620 --> 00:49:50,953
No, Irene's
bringing a dress,

1064
00:49:50,955 --> 00:49:52,754
and Richard's trying hard
to find a minister

1065
00:49:52,756 --> 00:49:54,223
that will
actually marry us.

1066
00:49:54,225 --> 00:49:56,124
It's harder to find someone
to marry us than I thought.

1067
00:49:56,126 --> 00:49:59,962
I have a unitarian.
How are you with unitarians?

1068
00:49:59,964 --> 00:50:01,196
Are they legal?

1069
00:50:01,198 --> 00:50:02,664
As a king's seal.

1070
00:50:02,666 --> 00:50:04,766
Oh.
Then unitarian it is.

1071
00:50:04,768 --> 00:50:07,035
Do you,
Richard Walter Burton,

1072
00:50:07,037 --> 00:50:10,205
take Elizabeth Rosemond Taylor
to be your wife?

1073
00:50:10,207 --> 00:50:11,773
I do.

1074
00:50:11,775 --> 00:50:13,742
And do you,
Elizabeth Rosemond Taylor,

1075
00:50:13,744 --> 00:50:15,777
take Richard
to be your husband?

1076
00:50:15,779 --> 00:50:17,045
I do.

1077
00:50:17,047 --> 00:50:19,548
By the power
invested in me,

1078
00:50:19,550 --> 00:50:22,217
I now pronounce you
man and wife.

1079
00:50:22,219 --> 00:50:24,086
You may kiss the bride.

1080
00:50:24,088 --> 00:50:25,254
That's it?

1081
00:50:25,256 --> 00:50:26,655
"That's it?"

1082
00:50:26,657 --> 00:50:29,057
