1245
00:58:17,661 --> 00:58:19,527
Wakey, wakey, wakey, wakey!

1246
00:58:19,529 --> 00:58:20,762
Come on, sleepyheads!

1247
00:58:20,764 --> 00:58:24,399
Wakey, wakey!

1248
00:58:24,401 --> 00:58:28,570
I have great news,
my lords and ladies.

1249
00:58:28,572 --> 00:58:33,675
Miss Elizabeth Taylor
and Mr. Richard Burton are...

1250
00:58:33,677 --> 00:58:35,777
Both nominated
for academy awards!

1251
00:58:35,779 --> 00:58:39,080
Yay!

1252
00:58:39,082 --> 00:58:42,751
That's fantastic, Richard --
two years in a row.

1253
00:58:42,753 --> 00:58:44,285
It's incredible.

1254
00:58:44,287 --> 00:58:46,621
And I'm already thinking
about what I'm going to wear.

1255
00:58:46,623 --> 00:58:47,722
[ Laughter ]

1256
00:58:47,724 --> 00:58:50,025
Richard.

1257
00:58:50,527 --> 00:58:51,693
You go.

1258
00:58:51,695 --> 00:58:53,695
I can't --
not after last time.

1259
00:58:53,697 --> 00:58:54,796
I just, uh...

1260
00:58:54,798 --> 00:58:57,065
Oh, no. We'll all stay here,
then, right?

1261
00:58:57,067 --> 00:58:58,233
We'll make a night of it.

1262
00:58:58,235 --> 00:58:59,567
[ Pan clattering ]

1263
00:58:59,569 --> 00:59:00,535
[ Laughs ]

1264
00:59:00,537 --> 00:59:02,137
Mommy,
can we dress nicely?

1265
00:59:02,139 --> 00:59:03,538
Of course we can,
my love.

1266
00:59:03,540 --> 00:59:06,041
I understood it.
I did.

1267
00:59:06,043 --> 00:59:07,509
Let's face it.

1268
00:59:07,511 --> 00:59:09,177
Those awards...

1269
00:59:09,179 --> 00:59:11,346
Four out of five people
are humiliated.

1270
00:59:11,348 --> 00:59:13,681
What worried me
was that Richard

1271
00:59:13,683 --> 00:59:16,351
wouldn't be there
if he won his Oscar.

1272
00:59:16,353 --> 00:59:18,186
And then when everyone on
"Virginia woolf" started to win,

1273
00:59:18,188 --> 00:59:19,721
it just...

1274
00:59:19,723 --> 00:59:22,323
Haskell WEXLER for best
cinematographer -- deservedly.

1275
00:59:22,325 --> 00:59:24,059
Yes, and Sandy Dennis
for best supporting.

1276
00:59:24,061 --> 00:59:25,393
Wonderful Sandy.

1277
00:59:25,395 --> 00:59:26,661
Woman:
<i>And the envelope, please.</i>

1278
00:59:26,663 --> 00:59:28,296
<i>And the winner is...</i>

1279
00:59:28,298 --> 00:59:29,731
<i>Elizabeth Taylor...</i>

1280
00:59:29,733 --> 00:59:31,599
[ All cheering ]

1281
00:59:37,273 --> 00:59:39,174
And then...

1282
00:59:39,176 --> 00:59:42,577
Man: <i>For best performance</i>
<i>by an actor,</i>

1283
00:59:42,579 --> 00:59:44,612
<i>the envelope, please.</i>

1284
00:59:44,614 --> 00:59:47,248
<i>And the winner is...</i>

1285
00:59:47,250 --> 00:59:49,784
<i>Paul Scofield,</i>
<i>"A Man For All Seasons."</i>

1286
00:59:49,786 --> 00:59:51,352
[ Click ]

1287
00:59:59,595 --> 01:00:02,497
Congratulations, Elizabeth.
Now you have two.

1288
01:00:04,100 --> 01:00:05,733
But now
I need to be alone,

1289
01:00:05,735 --> 01:00:09,270
because I am
a very, very poor loser.

1290
01:00:11,240 --> 01:00:13,108
Come on, guys.

1291
01:00:13,110 --> 01:00:15,276
Come on.

1292
01:00:23,419 --> 01:00:26,888
Scofield stayed
in the theater.

1293
01:00:26,890 --> 01:00:28,723
So what?

1294
01:00:28,725 --> 01:00:31,259
Probably lives in a damp flat
in east London.

1295
01:00:31,261 --> 01:00:32,427
[ Laughs ]

1296
01:00:33,863 --> 01:00:35,263
Oh, come on.

1297
01:00:35,265 --> 01:00:37,398
It's not like
you lost your job or any--

1298
01:00:37,400 --> 01:00:39,868
how the hell would you know
what I lost?!

1299
01:00:41,237 --> 01:00:43,671
