1810
01:25:30,225 --> 01:25:32,659
[ Indistinct shouting ]

1811
01:25:32,661 --> 01:25:34,794
So, when's the funeral
gonna be?

1812
01:25:34,796 --> 01:25:36,663
[ Shouting continues ]

1813
01:25:36,665 --> 01:25:37,931
Just one question,
please.

1814
01:25:37,933 --> 01:25:39,232
Sir, please!

1815
01:25:39,234 --> 01:25:40,867
At the request
of Richard's widow

1816
01:25:40,869 --> 01:25:42,769
and to avoid a media circus,

1817
01:25:42,771 --> 01:25:45,939
Miss Taylor will not attend
Richard Burton's funeral

1818
01:25:45,941 --> 01:25:48,274
and will not
be making a statement.

1819
01:25:48,276 --> 01:25:49,376
Thank you.

1820
01:25:49,378 --> 01:25:51,878
[ Bell tolling, birds chirping ]

1821
01:25:56,717 --> 01:25:58,251
[ Sighs ]

1822
01:25:59,820 --> 01:26:02,055
[ Indistinct talking ]

1823
01:26:05,660 --> 01:26:06,726
I'll get the police.

1824
01:26:09,697 --> 01:26:10,930
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

1825
01:26:10,932 --> 01:26:12,432
Please, please --
have some respect.

1826
01:26:12,434 --> 01:26:14,267
Please.

1827
01:26:18,739 --> 01:26:22,042
[ Voice breaking ] Do you know how
rarely we were ever truly alone?

1828
01:26:25,880 --> 01:26:28,348
[ Speaking French ]

1829
01:26:32,253 --> 01:26:34,087
[ Sniffles ]

1830
01:26:38,325 --> 01:26:41,027
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
Madame! Madame!

1831
01:26:41,029 --> 01:26:42,429
Oh, God, do you have
your pictures now?!

1832
01:26:42,431 --> 01:26:43,897
Do you?!

1833
01:26:43,899 --> 01:26:45,899
Can't you leave us alone?!

1834
01:26:45,901 --> 01:26:48,301
[ Man speaking French ]

1835
01:26:59,013 --> 01:27:01,381
[ Crying ]

1836
01:27:10,791 --> 01:27:12,192
Forever an ocean.

1837
01:27:13,761 --> 01:27:16,763
[ Voice breaking ]
Forever an ocean.

1838
01:27:16,765 --> 01:27:18,865
I think
we balanced each other out.

1839
01:27:18,867 --> 01:27:22,302
I think the balance was
what really meant the most.

1840
01:27:22,304 --> 01:27:23,737
[ Chuckles ]

1841
01:27:23,739 --> 01:27:27,407
I think that we both
understood each other.

1842
01:27:27,409 --> 01:27:30,043
And I don't think
we'd ever had that.

1843
01:27:32,346 --> 01:27:34,948
[ Voice breaking ] And without
him, I didn't know what to do.

1844
01:27:34,950 --> 01:27:37,517
[ Sniffles ]

1845
01:27:39,086 --> 01:27:42,455
I could feel
that he really loved me.

1846
01:27:42,457 --> 01:27:44,491
[ Sniffles ]

1847
01:27:44,493 --> 01:27:46,893
He just loved me.

1848
